Tainted food impacts at least 300 million Chinese people a year and could lead to a disease outbreak that exacts a huge social and economic toll, the Asian Development Bank warned Monday.
In recent years, China's actual food safety situation has not led one to be optimistic," the financial institute said in a report posted on its website.
The economic and social impact of the production of tainted foods is very large...diseases stemming from food can have a negative social impact and can even influence social stability."
